============================================================================
INTERPRETATION
============================================================================

  The VDR result is the exact answer for this discretization.
  The float result is the exact answer plus accumulated rounding.
  The drift column shows how much of the float answer is arithmetic
  noise vs physics.

  If this drift is in the millivolt range, it contaminates the
  threshold voltage prediction. At sub-3nm nodes where the total
  Vth variability budget is ~10-50 mV, float arithmetic noise
  consumes part of what engineers attribute to random dopant
  fluctuation.

  The symmetry test is definitive: a symmetric device MUST produce
  antisymmetric potential. VDR preserves this exactly. Float breaks
  it through asymmetric rounding accumulation in the Gummel loop.

